The City Futures Leaders Experience is your opportunity to learn more about what it means to be a leader whilst improving your soft and interpersonal skills as well as getting a direct insight from industry experts and leading companies in their fields.

The programme takes place across three half-days between the 16th-18th March 2022, with the first day taking place on campus (1pm-5pm) and days 2 & 3 (3pm-7pm) happening online. You will take part in both full-group sessions and small breakout rooms, where you will get a chance to build stronger connections with industry leaders and your peers.

Who could you hear from? During the programme, you will engage with leaders from organisations such as: 
‚Ä¢	Deloitte 
‚Ä¢	EY 
‚Ä¢	Oxfam 
‚Ä¢	Uber 
‚Ä¢	United Nations 

What organisational challenges have students explored in previous programmes? 
‚Ä¢	Increasing public trust in banks 
‚Ä¢	Improving educational standards 
‚Ä¢	Engaging young people in the arts 
‚Ä¢	Developing a small charity into a global brand 
