As a reminder, the majority of our campus will be closed on Monday 28 February, Tuesday 1 March and Wednesday 2 March, as a result of the industrial action called by UNISON. This is due to the limited number of colleagues in security roles available for work on these dates with the sufficient level of safety training. 

Unless your School confirms you have practical teaching sessions on these dates, or you require access to the study spaces or Library, please do not travel to campus on these dates.

During this time, you can continue to access our support services and library resources online. Our Northampton Square Library will be open (10am-5pm) if you urgently need to access library or study spaces on these days, and the Student Centre will be based on level 5 of the Library (10am-4pm) to support you. Please note, they will not be able to issue ID cards on these dates.

For more information, read our Student Hub page: http://ow.ly/mSUW50I5H4P

